import cv2
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# List of image paths
image_paths = [
    "C:\\Users\\user\\Desktop\\binary images\\img1.png",
    "C:\\Users\\user\\Desktop\\binary images\\img2.png",
    "C:\\Users\\user\\Desktop\\binary images\\img3.png"
]

# 3x3 kernel for morphology
kernel = np.ones((3,3), np.uint8)

for path in image_paths:
    # Load each image
    img = cv2.imread(path, cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

    # Check if image is loaded
    if img is None:
        print(f"Image not found! Check the path: {path}")
        continue

    # Show original
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f"Original Image: {path}")
    plt.show()

    # Apply erosion
    erosion = cv2.erode(img, kernel, iterations=1)
    plt.imshow(erosion, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("After Erosion")
    plt.show()

    # Apply dilation
    dilation = cv2.dilate(erosion, kernel, iterations=1)
    plt.imshow(dilation, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("After Dilation")
    plt.show()

    # Opening operation
    opening = cv2.morphologyEx(img, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel)
    plt.imshow(opening, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("After Opening")
    plt.show()

    # Closing operation
    closing = cv2.morphologyEx(img, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel)
    plt.imshow(closing, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("After Closing")
    plt.show()
